      "content": "Your fear that there is nothing left to reclaim feels incredibly heavy, but the empty space you describe isn't a void to be filled; it is often a necessary pause that allows the noise of the past to finally settle. Just because a specific plotline ends doesn't mean the story of your life stops, even if the current chapter leaves everything quiet and still. It is okay to simply exist in that quiet without demanding it have meaning, even just for a moment.",
